The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality on Sunday water supply has been reduced by 30% because of the Kirkwood canal collapse on Thursday last week."All residents urgently requested to reduce water usage," the municipality said."We envisage that as from Monday evening the water supply to the eastern and northern parts of the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality will be affected."These are the areas that will be affected:- Despatch Parts Uitenhage Motherwell Ikamvelihle Coega Wells Estate Bluewater Bay Bloemendal Bethelsdorp Chatty Colchester"All residents of NMBM are requested to reduce water usage to a minimum, so that the is a fare share across the metro, and prevent any possible water outages in the above listed areas."